Ask HN: Autistic employees think they’re better than everyone
text: I’m working with a 10x engineer who’s most likely autistic and produces more than everyone else. He’s taking the team down because he steals work from others and nobody can learn the codebase. It’s also really bad code so he’s the only one that can understand it and refuses to document or explain what is going on. Is it rare or is it a common situation?
